Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.70,0:00:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's go back to your life frame.\NYou sound like quite very successful, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist, there are lots of people wants to see you\Nand you're almost overwhelmed by this number of people
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.50,0:00:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to see you and you said you're so frustrated\Nbecause in spite of such a big need to seeing you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you can only deal one patient at a time.\NSo you start to wondering is there any other way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.32,0:00:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you can address this problem in a more collective way,\Nwhatever I can say.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.56,0:00:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So then you eventually having seven years of your own time.\NSo maybe we can go back that more period
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.70,0:01:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell me more about what has been going on\Nin your own inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.47,0:01:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this phase where you're in love with everyone\Nand people become healed by this love, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.56,0:01:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that recognition of the truth of who they are\Nand loving them on that level that heals the inner pain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.78,0:01:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and suffering from which they came.\NAnd they came in great droves, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.75,0:01:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,like I think I told you they were backed up\Nin all the major airports in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.11,0:01:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw people from every country in the world.\NThey used to fly from Paris once a month to see me,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.43,0:01:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, things like that.\NSo yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.85,0:01:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheer volume.\NThe sheer volume of it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.72,0:01:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To see so many patients, you know,\Nyou can only see so many in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.00,0:01:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would see 40 at the hospital\Nand then go to the clinic and see more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.86,0:02:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in the evening I would give talks\Nor things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.06,0:02:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're still only reaching, you know,\Nliterally a certain limited number of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.99,0:02:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though I used to give lectures and classes\Nand whenever I gave a lecture there would always be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.01,0:02:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand people.\NAnd they always hired a whole for a thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was always filled.\NBut even then it seemed like, see,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.20,0:02:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I had seen the totality of human suffering.\NAs I say, it was like revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.74,0:02:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And that still remained to be addressed.\NThese were specific people suffering specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.23,0:02:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was still the general problem.\NOne day I was walking down Fifth Avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was walking down Fifth Avenue.\NI had an apartment at 952 Fifth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.14,0:03:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was in that incredible state and I was aware\Nthat the negativity of the city, the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the total negativity of New York City is so immense\Nthat it would literally blow the city apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.19,0:03:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Except for the fact that there is that\Nwhich counterbalances it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.85,0:03:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To counterbalance the total negativity of New York City\Nwhich is almost 13 million people only requires
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a few individuals that calibrate maybe 700, 800, see?\NTheir power, so it's like the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and its expression as the power of that\Nwhich is universally loving counterbalances
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,all the negativity.\NBut it radiates out from some individuals you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.73,0:04:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment I was walking down and I was,\NI was that energy that was counterbalancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.18,0:04:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And another man, he looked like the world might think\Nhe was a bum, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.36,0:04:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Walked down Fifth Avenue down the sidewalk\Nand we looked at each other and recognized each other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.12,0:04:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for who we were.\NI think there was maybe two people at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.99,0:04:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalancing that total negativity.\NAnd he was a sage and we looked at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.87,0:04:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and then passed on, you know?\NThere's nothing to say, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to learn how to manufacture talkingness\Nwas part of the project and I love the world
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.18,0:04:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw that the greatest gift one can give mankind\Nis to perfect oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.79,0:04:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I say oneself, I'm talking about\Nto perfect that state, to perfect that state
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:05:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look at it in silence and to sense out of that state\Nand to spiritually sense out of that to be a perfect mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the world of the shining forth of divinity\Nthrough the expression of creation itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the perfect mirror back to that, to mankind\Nwas what I was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I left the distraction of the city and moved into a\Nrather large home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.97,0:06:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was a monastery for one person, myself.\NAnd I decorated it with all the various ways to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.66,0:06:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I had all the holy books of all the world's religions there.\NBecause each one, you know, is its own pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.96,0:06:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's 10,000 paths to God.\NSo you spent most of the time for reading and meditation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.67,0:06:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not reading.\NI never read anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You would call it meditation.\NJust being in that state is itself the meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the meditation goes on continuously.\NWhat the world would call a meditation is always going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going on now.\NBecause this talkingness is coming out of the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,through a certain volition which I train myself to do\Nto express back out that which is not expressible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.79,0:07:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All what I'm talking about is not actually expressible.\NWhat can you say about silence? Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I'm trying to get a sense of what you mean by perfecting yourself.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.45,0:07:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's very hard to understand.\NAt that point it's more a subtle shifting of awareness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be more like the surface of the ocean is still,\Nand then there's a slight rise a little bit like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It does it of its own, and one is reflecting slightly differently.\NMaybe the moon has brought it up a little higher at this end of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.44,0:07:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like that is happening.\NWell, I just remember the cathedral rock
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.20,0:08:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because this rock looks very different from which angle you're looking at.\NAnd I don't know which form is the perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.26,0:08:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but maybe I can imagine what you're saying to me in that sense.\NBecause I like one particular angle of cathedral rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.26,0:08:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's coming like, boom.\NYes, that's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.90,0:08:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind of sense.\NAnyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.93,0:08:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When one is addressing God, you want to know how it is with myself now, yes?\NThere's no verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.16,0:08:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no visualization.\NIt has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.47,0:09:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like one reflects a need of the world, of humanity,\Nthrough oneself so that God is presented with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.87,0:09:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more almost like a mudra.\NIt would be more like if I want to know God's will, it's something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.64,0:09:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I just go like, in my spiritual body,\NI just go like so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be how one asks the question, you see?\NIt would be like more a posture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.39,0:09:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So one's posture speaks to God\Nbecause there's no verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.03,0:09:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no visualization necessary\Nin that God knows all that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which knows all that is knows what's being asked\Nwithout having to ask it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.16,0:10:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be like saying to God,\Nyou're so stupid, I have to verbalize this for you to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.16,0:10:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No such thing is necessary.\NWell, what you're talking reminds me of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.48,0:10:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe 10,000 Buddha's posture.\NIf you go to any of these Buddhist temples,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.48,0:10:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all different forms and sitting pose\Nof Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, you see, as I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is unmanifest is beyond form.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.69,0:10:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The next level down would be\Nexistence versus nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then below existence itself\Nwould be existence as life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.45,0:10:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there are the various hierarchies.\NSo you might say, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.12,0:10:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for example, as is commonly understood,\Nthere would be God
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.28,0:11:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there would be the various levels of heaven.\NThere would be the archangels,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the great archangels,\Nthe Lord Jesus Christ, the great avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there would be ordinary angels.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.08,0:11:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like God expresses itself through us\Nlike a step-down transformer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,until you get to physical expression of humanness\Non the planet as an avatar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.59,0:11:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at a thousand.\NThen you get to the very advanced consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.72,0:11:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 900s.\NI don't know anybody in the 900s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.72,0:11:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't found anything in the 900s.\NWell, I haven't researched it, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.72,0:11:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get people down through the gurus\Nand down through the spiritual teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.39,0:11:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and enlightened beings\Nand then the teachers in the high 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the people in whom the heart is just opening.\NAnd then you get the intelligent people in the 400s
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.06,0:11:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you get the salt of the earth\Nthat are in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.06,0:12:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hard workers in the 200s\Nand then animal energy itself in the 100s.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.76,0:12:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you understand what I'm saying?\NUntil you finally get down to the one-celled organism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.86,0:12:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these levels.\NSo at each level, one serves differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.37,0:12:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One serves differently.\NOne serves God by tending the sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If one's consciousness is at 200,\Nthen to do one's duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And to tend the sheep is serving God at 200.\NIt's serving life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.02,0:12:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you are really reaching the same level of consciousness,\Nprobably it's almost an impossible possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.02,0:12:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to describing and having a conversation of it.\NSo it's probably my limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.02,0:12:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, once people hear about all these stories,\Nthen they start to wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.02,0:13:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,how does one reach this state of awareness?\NOh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.02,0:13:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's talk about,\Nyou briefly mentioned about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the way people can develop\Nor the way people can evolve themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.05,0:13:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think,\Nyou see there's various yogas
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,classically described throughout the centuries.\NKali yoga, I mean all these various yogas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.89,0:13:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Raja yoga, all these things.\NBhakti yoga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.46,0:13:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NActually, one does all of them at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.00,0:13:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think the whole thing hinges on willingness.\NFirst of all, humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.96,0:13:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the suspicion that there is something other than\Nwhat the world thinks is reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.96,0:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that has to be there first.\NYou begin to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.96,0:14:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,huh, maybe things are somewhat different.\NFor one thing, you see that people are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.96,0:14:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see one person gets angry in the situation.\NAnother person gets sad in the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Another person is unaffected by it.\NYou see that some people are very positive
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and some people are very negative.\NSo you begin to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.12,0:14:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,huh, there is some kind of variation possible.\NThere must be other ways of experiencing life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.12,0:14:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you're not always upset.\NSo some people begin to desire peace and harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think there has to be the desire to love,\Nthe desire to forgive people,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.21,0:14:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the wish to see things differently,\Nto be dissatisfied with negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.53,0:14:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So you become dissatisfied with negativity.\NYou say, I'm tired of being angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.53,0:14:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of always wanting something.\NI'm tired of being frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.53,0:14:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of all that.\NThere must be a better way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you start seeking a spiritual pathway.\NWell, then there's taking spiritual teachings seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.56,0:15:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, if judgment is mine, saith the Lord,\Nwhen you become spiritually oriented,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to take that seriously.\NAnd you say, well, God is saying judgment is up to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not up to you.\NSo you begin to be willing to let go judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think a certain desire to be loving towards other creatures,\Na certain respect for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.19,0:15:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a point at which one perfects one's sense of mastery\Nand masculinity to be the great hunter, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.35,0:15:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is fine when you're 16.\NBut then there comes the day
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look through the telescopic side of the rifle\Nand you see the stag standing there,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.70,0:15:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you're struck.\NBy its incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.70,0:15:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more strikingly beautiful\Nthan to see a stag standing there in the middle of a meadow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,still as a statue.\NAnd suddenly, BOOM!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:16:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Its incredible beauty strikes you.\NAnd you see it wants life as much as you want life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.08,0:16:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Its desire for life, it struggles for life the same as you.\NYou see yourself in that stag
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.37,0:16:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize you cannot pull the trigger anymore\Nbecause you're killing life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.60,0:16:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're killing yourself.\NThat which you are is just standing out there as that stag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize, you know,\Nif you destroy his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.92,0:16:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you've really just destroyed your own.\NHow could you love?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.40,0:16:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So your capacity to love has to increase.\NThe yoga that I follow, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.25,0:16:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to use classic language,\Nthe yoga that I follow has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.25,0:16:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,moving from duality to non-duality.\NIt's the pathway of non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that it is not suitable for the average spiritual seeker\Nin this Kali Yuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.21,0:16:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that it's not.\NIt is said that the negativity and destruction of the world is so intense
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.34,0:17:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that the capacity to leave the gravity of it\Nand project off into the stratosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.82,0:17:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is the chances of successfully doing that are not very great.\NIt is suggested generally by spiritual teachers that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,karma yoga, the yoga of loving service,\Nselfless service is more suitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity is the pathway of selfless service.\NMahayana Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure Land Buddhism\Nare the ways that are suitable for most people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.75,0:17:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus Christ said that too, you know.\NIt's like Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.75,0:17:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,your chances of reaching enlightenment\Nare so slim in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.88,0:17:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that what you'd best do is\Npurify yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.64,0:17:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,become as loving as you can,\Nand when you leave the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.64,0:17:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you will go to heaven.\NAnd in heaven we have higher spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:18:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't all that negativity.\NAnd from heaven then you can progress farther.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.80,0:18:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NPure Land Buddhism says the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.80,0:18:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You believe in Buddha\Nand then he's your savior.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you die, you go to the pure land,\Nwhich is like a heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me, Jesus Christ was always very practical.\NHe said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.06,0:18:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not very likely\Nthat the average person in his daily life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to become enlightened,\Nbut he could become quite spiritually advanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.12,0:18:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,become a very loving creature\Nand suitable for heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In my own condition,\Ndon't forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.24,0:18:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,these things began of their own.\NWhen I was three or four,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.24,0:18:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was suddenly confronted.\NAnd there was probably,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I can surmise,\Nthere was probably many lifetimes of meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.88,0:18:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I didn't mention,\Nyou know, in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.88,0:18:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I meditated for some 25 years,\Nyou know, on a regular basis without fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.17,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when I had the biggest practice in New York\Nor maybe even in the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.40,0:19:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I still meditated from, you know,\N5 in the morning until 5.30 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.40,0:19:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I meditated again from 5.30 to 7, perhaps.\NSo for 20 years I did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.40,0:19:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when I came out by myself,\NI was in a meditative state,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a meditative state all the time.\NWell, what facilitated going into
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these rather incredible experiences was\Nthe technique is really that of surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really a part of the love of God.\NIf you love God enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.01,0:19:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,if Jesus Christ stood here and said,\Nfor me and for the salvation of all mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.01,0:19:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to give up your ego\Nand the vanity of thinking that you know anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.01,0:19:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,would you be willing to do it?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.01,0:19:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the presence of that great being,\Nyou'd say, anything you want, Lord, anything, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.78,0:20:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So there has to be the letting go of the vanity of,\Nwhat should we say, energizing one's ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.92,0:20:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of believing in one's ego,\Nof thinking that one's thoughts have any value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.96,0:20:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One's thoughts have no value, by the way.\NIt just may sound surprising,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.96,0:20:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but one's thoughts have no value whatsoever.\NNor do they originate from an individual personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.96,0:20:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no doer behind the deeds,\Nand there is no thinker behind the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts think themselves.\NThey don't need you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.05,0:20:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the body goes about its business.\NYou saw the body ever since you've been here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.05,0:20:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's going about its business, don't you?\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.05,0:20:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It sits here properly.\NIt does what it's supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's the way the universe interacts with itself.\NSo the universe is almost like a bunch of magnets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.21,0:20:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Each magnet has its own function.\NIt has its own polarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.21,0:21:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and its own power of magnetism.\NAnd so if all these magnets you see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.21,0:21:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all position themselves with each other\Nbased on their own polarity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.21,0:21:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and based on their own degree of power,\Nthose magnets are all doing it of their own self.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the energy that I put out\Nand the energy that you put out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.07,0:21:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so the energy that you put out\Nwas attracted to the energy that I put out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.07,0:21:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why we're here today.\NIt's like two magnets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.07,0:21:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NSo it doesn't require an individual Yoon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.07,0:21:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or an individual David\Nto make any decision about such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.07,0:21:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It just automatically gravitates.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.45,0:21:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we're going in the same direction.\NSo you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm going in the same direction.\NTell me what you know
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.45,0:21:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because that will assist me on my pathway.\NAnd my pathway is to help you on your pathway
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.52,0:21:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in whatever way my sharing could help you.\NSo we serve each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.52,0:22:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have a common goal eventually.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.51,0:22:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens then is this,\Nperhaps, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.62,0:22:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,many people hit,\Nthey spiritually advance
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.62,0:22:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when they so-called hit bottom.\NWhat that means is you have followed the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.62,0:22:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to its idiotic end.\NIf you follow the ego with great intensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.62,0:22:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it will eventually bring you to great disaster.\NAnd when it's, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.62,0:22:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,your life becomes the result\Nof your own best thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.62,0:22:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you are in a state of catastrophe\Nof one kind or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.62,0:22:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's at that point\Nthat some people get humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.62,0:22:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They say,\NWell, there must be a better way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people might even call on God at that point\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.62,0:22:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I think I'm in trouble.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.78,0:22:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in my own case,\NI gravitated to teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.96,0:22:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say,\Nlike Ramana Maharshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.19,0:22:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I read Ramana Maharshi,\NI suddenly knew
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.19,0:23:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that he knew what he was talking about\Nbecause I had already experienced that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.19,0:23:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The states that I read about\Nhad already occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.05,0:23:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when I read about them.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.05,0:23:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it was very interesting to me\Nthat other people had experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.05,0:23:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,these same states.\NThe way the state came about,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.39,0:23:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say I told you about one time,\N11 days I surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.39,0:23:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the technique then,\Nthe technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.25,0:23:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,people are interested\Nin spiritual meditative techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.25,0:23:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do when you meditate?\NWhat you do when you meditate
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is each thought\Nas it arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.35,0:23:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you surrender it to God.\NEach thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,each feeling,\Neach sensation,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.86,0:23:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you let go wanting to change anything.\NNow, if everything is absolutely perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.86,0:23:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as the spiritual,\Nas the teachers say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.24,0:23:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm a teacher at this moment,\NI tell you everything is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.24,0:23:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing has to change.\NYou don't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.44,0:23:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You are already perfect.\NAlright, if that is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.72,0:24:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then there is no point\Nto make anything different
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.04,0:24:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,than what it is.\NSo the next move one would make
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.14,0:24:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if one has humility\Nand listens to the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.14,0:24:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is to say,\Nconsequently my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have to do anything.\NIt doesn't have to think anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.72,0:24:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens is,\Nis the mind begins to surrender itself
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.13,0:24:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as it unfolds.\NSo let's say you sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.29,0:24:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and go start to meditate\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.29,0:24:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to experience\Nthe infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.42,0:24:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple.\NIt's a very simple thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.68,0:24:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is\Nabsolutely and fixedly focus
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.96,0:24:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like a razor,\Nlike a laser beam
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.00,0:24:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on each thought as it arises.\NAlright, as you surrender each thought
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.44,0:24:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and feeling and impulse\Nas it arises to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.44,0:24:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,at first you surrender whole stories.\NI think I told you people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.79,0:25:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,think they have problems.\NThey have problems
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.04,0:25:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because they read a story\Nin their head.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.04,0:25:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we talk about that?\NYeah, we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.04,0:25:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We did.\NAlright, so we explain also
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.04,0:25:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that nobody has a problem.\NThat as long as you live
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.04,0:25:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in this instant,\Nin this instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.04,0:25:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody has a problem\Nin this whole universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.04,0:25:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has a problem\Nthis instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.04,0:25:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so what happens is\Nas you let go the stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.68,0:25:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as you see how the mind\Ncreates stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.68,0:25:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin living in the stop frame\Nof this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.00,0:25:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will see that the mind\Nlikes to create thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.35,0:25:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So first you surrender stories.\NThen you surrender paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.35,0:25:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you surrender sentences.\NYou don't allow the sentence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.35,0:25:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to even complete itself.\NIf it's worthless,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.35,0:25:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,then why complete the sentence?\NIf your thoughts don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.41,0:25:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,any intrinsic value,\Nif they're just
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.05,0:25:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,belong to the world\Nand not even yours to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.05,0:26:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, they're creations of the ego\Nand the energy fuels of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.05,0:26:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then there's no point to perfect it.\NAlright, so the first one surrenders
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.22,0:26:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,one stops creating stories.\NThen one stops creating paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.22,0:26:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One stops creating sentences.\NOne stops creating phrases.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.28,0:26:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will see that languaging\Nin the form of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.15,0:26:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from an energy.\NThere's like an energy in the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.15,0:26:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that is constantly creating\Nlike a stream of thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.21,0:26:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you watch thoughts\Ngoing through consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.21,0:26:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,like goldfish through a bowl.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.21,0:26:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts are like goldfish.\NBut what you are is the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.44,0:26:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the goldfish.\NSo the unenlightened person thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.44,0:26:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the goldfish.\NI am my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.44,0:26:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I am this worry.\NI am this fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.44,0:26:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I am this regret.\NYou begin to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.94,0:27:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to identify\Nwhere is consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.94,0:27:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is what is witnessing\Nthese thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.20,0:27:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So thoughts are flowing through\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.20,0:27:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and consciousness itself is invisible\Nand has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.42,0:27:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to identify\Nwith the observer
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.74,0:27:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of that which is observed.\NAnybody who does meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.74,0:27:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,knows what I'm saying already.\NBut this energy behind thought
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.47,0:27:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is itself formless.\NIt does not have,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.84,0:27:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like this energy wants to come up\Nand then it begins to express itself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.84,0:27:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as a thought.\NAnd at that point
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.04,0:27:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you let go wanting to have the thought.\NSo you're constantly surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.55,0:27:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your thinkingness.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.36,0:27:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice that what the mind does\Nis it tries to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.36,0:28:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the next split second.\NWhat your mind is doing right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.00,0:28:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ewan,\Nis anticipating the next second.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.99,0:28:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear your mind clanking away\Nand it's trying to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.34,0:28:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the next moment.\NIt thinks it has to.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.52,0:28:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks it has to\Nin order to survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.77,0:28:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to master.\NSo if you watch what your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.77,0:28:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is really doing,\Nyou'll see it's always trying
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.77,0:28:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to get one up on the next instant.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.09,0:28:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,By next instant,\NI'm talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.09,0:28:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a tenth of a second.\NSo what a person is experiencing,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.21,0:28:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they're never experiencing reality.\NWhat they're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.85,0:28:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ego's interpretation of reality.\NSo like an audio system,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.85,0:28:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,there's what's called a monitor.\NSo just as you tape something,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.85,0:28:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just as you tape a program on the tape,\Nthe monitor feeds into your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.98,0:28:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard what was just required\Nrecorded a split second ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.98,0:29:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not hearing\Nthe program source.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.36,0:29:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hearing what was just recorded.\NThis is what the average person
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.20,0:29:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is experiencing,\Nis the monitor tape
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.32,0:29:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego's interpretation of events.\NThey're not experiencing events
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.71,0:29:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as they are in reality.\NThey're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.71,0:29:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego's interpretation.\NSo as this thinkingness begins to recede,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.57,0:29:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no longer a desire to think.\NThere's no longer a desire to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.57,0:29:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that thinkingness itself\Nis a vanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.85,0:29:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's like a violation\Nof the true nature of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.81,0:29:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like I negate God's Godness,\Ntherefore I have to think myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.76,0:29:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\NGod's not going to reveal to me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.76,0:29:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what I need to know.\NI got to go out there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.76,0:30:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and one up on God.\NSo what the ego's really doing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.76,0:30:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is supplanting God.\NYou begin to see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.11,0:30:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what the ego's up to\Nis to supplant God, replace God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.43,0:30:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want truth revealed to me.\NOh no, I'll make up my own truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.36,0:30:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lack of trust of God.\NAnd so this mind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.96,0:30:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is always anticipating.\NEventually the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.51,0:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as you watch it,\Nit's like you get earlier and earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.51,0:30:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,into the formation of thought itself.\NAs I say, first sentences,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.31,0:30:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean stories go, paragraphs go,\Nsentences go, concepts go, words go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.37,0:30:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The word begins to come up like dog.\NJust as the D and the O start to come up,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.61,0:30:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it's going to become dog.\NYou catch it already
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.77,0:30:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,before it even becomes dog\Nand let go the desire
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.84,0:31:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a thought.\NTo refunction in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.72,0:31:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to will ordinariness.\NI asked God to be ordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.42,0:31:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can't be of much good in the world\Nif you are unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.27,0:31:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.27,0:31:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're peculiar,\Nif you're not,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.97,0:31:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're odd.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.97,0:31:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the prejudice of the ego is such
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.97,0:31:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that I know that\Nto reemerge into the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.16,0:31:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to be ordinary.\NSo I'm just an ordinary doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.16,0:31:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,just an ordinary psychiatrist.\NAnd,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.36,0:31:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever I teach,\NI'm just an ordinary teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.36,0:31:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just ordinary.\NNow, in the research that I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.09,0:32:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing I noticed was that\Nyou could calibrate the energy level
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.22,0:32:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of a person the instant they were born.\NThe infant in the nursery,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.22,0:32:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute they're born.\NIn fact, you can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.22,0:32:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy level of the fetus\Nbefore it even emerges into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.22,0:32:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get that this child is born\Nwith an energy field of 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.21,0:32:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This child is born\Nat 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.21,0:32:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This child is born at 550.\NI don't know what I was born at.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.21,0:32:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked that.\NBut perhaps born,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.44,0:32:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nat an already advanced state
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.44,0:32:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.44,0:32:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.24,0:32:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings up the question\Nof the so-called bottom-up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.24,0:32:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and top-down discourse\Nin,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.24,0:32:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nthere's a,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.52,0:32:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there was been two conferences\Non consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.00,0:32:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at the University of Tucson.\NThe first one I went to,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.48,0:32:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the last one was also\Nthe spring of this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.48,0:33:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And this brings,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.15,0:33:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you see this life\Nthat creates the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.15,0:33:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Life,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.31,0:33:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite source\Nof all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.31,0:33:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is formlessness.\NIt is out of form,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.31,0:33:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,only formlessness\Nhas the power
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.31,0:33:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to create form.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.50,0:33:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the Godhead\Narises God,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.50,0:33:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,arises all of creation,\Narises the avatar,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.50,0:33:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,arises the,\Nspiritually aware people,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.53,0:33:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,arises the ordinary people,\Narises the animal kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.53,0:33:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,arises all of nature.\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.53,0:33:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NIt starts from the top down,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.53,0:33:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah?\NThe strict materialist says,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.13,0:33:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,oh no,\Norganisms,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.52,0:33:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,chemicals\Nrearrange themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.52,0:33:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\Nand created the,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.52,0:33:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the necessities for life\Nand then life,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.52,0:33:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,some,\Nlike spontaneous combustion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.52,0:33:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly came forth.\NAnd then life evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.52,0:33:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,through Darwinian evolution,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.52,0:33:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nto create
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.52,0:33:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what they consider\Nthe highest level
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.61,0:33:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything\Nthe human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.61,0:34:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,see?\NThis is a limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.90,0:34:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,very limited perception.\NWe have to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.96,0:34:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,how is it\Nthat various people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.20,0:34:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate\Ndifferent levels
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.20,0:34:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness\Nright at the moment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.20,0:34:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of birth?\NAnd I would leave
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.20,0:34:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the viewer\Nto,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.33,0:34:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to answer that himself.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.33,0:34:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,one explanation\Nwould be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.91,0:34:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that life\Ncontinues on
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.91,0:34:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant\Nof physical bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.71,0:34:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nphysical bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.71,0:34:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that life\Ntakes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.84,0:34:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,expression\Nsequentially
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.84,0:34:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of various bodies\Nto,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.16,0:34:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's say\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.16,0:34:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,exists\Nindependently
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.16,0:34:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of physicality.\NThen consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.25,0:34:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,seeks to learn\Nnew lessons
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.25,0:34:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nevolve
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.25,0:34:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NSo it needs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.25,0:34:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,bodies\Nto act
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.25,0:34:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out\Nin
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.25,0:34:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.57,0:34:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the state,\Nin my state
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.57,0:34:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no time.\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.08,0:35:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,thousand years\Nor a second
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.08,0:35:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are all the same\Nto me,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.31,0:35:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,makes no difference.\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.17,0:35:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,five years\Nsomebody says
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.17,0:35:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see you\Nin ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.91,0:35:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no problem.\NIf I see,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.91,0:35:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't seen somebody\Nin fifty years
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.91,0:35:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I see them\Nit's the same
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.15,0:35:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as I just saw them\Na second ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.15,0:35:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness\Nthen is outside
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.92,0:35:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of time\Nand space.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.92,0:35:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's say\Nit wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.92,0:35:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,express itself\Nin time
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.64,0:35:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and space\Nit has to have
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.64,0:35:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a physical body\Nand a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.64,0:35:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would be\Nfitting for that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.64,0:35:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.64,0:35:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for that being.\NSo if in this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.25,0:35:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,life time\Nmy spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.38,0:35:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose\Nwas to clarify
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.38,0:35:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,God\Nas void
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.82,0:35:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,versus\NGod
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.82,0:35:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as allness\Nthen I would pick
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.20,0:35:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain\Nlifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.20,0:35:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and way\Nof being
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.32,0:36:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that I would\Nconfront
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.32,0:36:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,myself\Nwith that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.48,0:36:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,See.\NSo it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.48,0:36:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like each being\Nconfronts itself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.48,0:36:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with whatever\NIt feels it has to learn to evolve to a greater state of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.97,0:36:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than picking sequentially physical bodies, it would be hard to say how else it could be done.\NAll right, the Buddha told us that at one point he remembered all of his previous lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.56,0:36:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.92,0:36:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Many, many.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.68,0:36:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole idea of reincarnation only arises if you see yourself as a separate ego.\NOtherwise, the question doesn't arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.56,0:36:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that which I am is and has been and will forever be all that is.\NIn as much as I am, all that ever is, has been, or could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.67,0:37:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had previous lives, it would only be...\NYou see, the difficulty of reincarnation is you have to create the artifact of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.38,0:37:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in reality, there is no time.\NSo, how can we describe form outside of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.60,0:37:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's where the example of the hologram becomes useful.\NNow, you're familiar with a hologram.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.60,0:37:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's projected by a laser beam and a photographic...\NGoing through this plate, the two intersect and recreate three-dimensionally in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.19,0:37:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you fracture the photographic plate, any tiny fragment of the photographic plate,\Nwhen you put the laser beam through it, will recreate the entire hologram all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.33,0:37:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NIf you walk through a hologram, let's say we have a hologram of somebody walking, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.86,0:38:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you look at the hologram, if you stand on this side of the hologram, you see the person like this.\NNow, as you move back around the hologram, the person moves like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.85,0:38:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, as you move back through the hologram, the person is sitting like so.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.68,0:38:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, in reality, the person is not sitting in any one of those spaces.\NAt the same time, he is actually coexisting in all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.54,0:38:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.93,0:38:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, time would just be a moving point of perception.\NIs this part of the hologram more advanced in time than this part of the hologram?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.17,0:38:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThey coexist simultaneously outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.99,0:38:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the world as people experience it then is from a fixed point of perception,\Nthey walk through a hologram of a universe which has already occurred and is already total and complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.11,0:38:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd think they see movement and change and the progression of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.15,0:39:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No such thing is going on.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.54,0:39:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If I am all things that have ever been, then, and if there's no discontinuity between one thing and another,\Nthen holographically, there is no discontinuity between lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.10,0:39:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.26,0:39:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NConsciousness evolves through.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.78,0:39:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say I was once a...\NWe could do the ancient, the Hindu belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.42,0:39:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I came up as a frog, then an amphibian, then I became a kitty cat,\Nand then I learned to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.86,0:39:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I learned to live.\NAnd then I learned to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.02,0:39:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I learned to live.\NAnd then I learned to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.12,0:39:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say the dog and the cat are learning to love.\NThey certainly know how to love better than many humans, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.76,0:39:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're perfecting the emotional body and the capacity to love\Nand how to master an animal body and a warm-blooded physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.26,0:39:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So this evolution, so if we take the evolution of all of creation\Nand we see it as continuous, one continuous hologram,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.86,0:40:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no separate lifetimes.\NYou aren't one lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.92,0:40:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This one lifetime, this one lifetime, this.\NThat would be only a point, artificial point of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.94,0:40:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOne is all that ever has been since the beginning of all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.91,0:40:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and one will be all that ever will be throughout all of time.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.86,0:40:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you look back at specific remembrances of other existences in other times?\NIf at this point in the hologram you could look back at some other point in the hologram,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.16,0:40:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you would say, well, that's a separate lifetime.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.32,0:40:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.42,0:40:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.84,0:40:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.88,0:40:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.92,0:40:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.00,0:40:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.04,0:40:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.04,0:40:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NBut it would be a different frame, a different frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.22,0:40:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So as the movie unfolds, that's a different frame.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.72,0:40:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.03,0:40:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, in your own meditation, is there any, any images you have noticed?\NLet's, let's clarify the Western, um, belief system about reincarnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.67,0:41:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, all the world believes about, all the world believes in reincarnation\Nwith the exception of the Western world, dominated by Judo, Greek, Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.31,0:41:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,culture didn't exist in their belief system. Does Christianity believe in it? Karma? Oh,\Nyes, it does. It doesn't call it karma. It doesn't use a Sanskrit term. It believes that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.90,0:41:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ said, as ye do, so you shall reap. Oh, yes. There are great consequences\Nto everything, and that the Lord has counted every hair on your head, and that no sparrow
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.00,0:41:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,falls without God knowing about it. Therefore, Christianity believes very heavily in karma.\NIn fact, it's because of karma that everybody gets obsessed about sin and avoiding sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.72,0:42:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because karmically, you're creating a future for yourself. So, when you leave the physical\Nbody, you're going to go to limbo, which is sort of a nowhere place,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.54,0:42:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or you're going to go to a place where you're going to go to a place where you're going to\Nheaven. There's various hierarchies in heaven. Everybody knows that. Or you're going to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.36,0:42:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hell, and there's various levels of hell. So, Dante described, you know, the heavens and the\Nhells. Oh, yes. So, Christians believe very much in karma. They say, you know, and that's what all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.40,0:42:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the praying is about, and all the obsessing, and all the religiosity is because everybody wants to\Nbe sure to go to heaven, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.06,0:42:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what all the praying to the saints is about. Please help me, help me saying something\Nor other to get into heaven, you know. Everybody worries about getting into heaven. So, everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.84,0:43:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then is saying that my actions will determine a later lifetime in a different form. My soul,\Nmy spirit will continue on despite the demise of this physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.25,0:43:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will have a lifetime, not only that, but it will have a long lifetime. People think when you go to\Nheaven, you go there forever, or when you go to hell, you go to hell forever, etc. They not only project
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.25,0:43:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,another lifetime, they project a time span.\NSo, what you're saying is basically the wisdom mind understands...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.88,0:43:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The wisdom mind does believe in karma, yeah. And of course, you're going to reincarnate in a spirit body in a\Ndifferent realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.04,0:43:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOh, yes. But what it only...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.91,0:43:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhat it only focuses on is this particular lifetime. Well, that could be a defect of Christian teaching, I don't know, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.49,0:43:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said in the beginning, Jesus Christ calibrates at 1,000, as does the other great avatars. The Buddha calibrates at 1,000.\NThe Buddha says, yes, there are many lifetimes. Well, we don't know what Christ said about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.49,0:44:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take the New Testament and you boil down, you know, and some New Testament is printed, what Christ said is in red.\NIf you take out all of the New Testament and you boil down, you know, some New Testament is printed, what Christ said is in red.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.91,0:44:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take out all the things that are in red, only what Jesus Christ said, and put them together, you don't have much at all.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.00,0:44:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. And four of the Gospels are repetitious. So you could really boil down all four Gospels, because they're all telling the same story about the same events from a different witness's viewpoint.\NIf you boil it all down, you have only really a few pages of what Jesus Christ said. So you have no idea what he said about reincarnation. You have no idea what he said about the equality of women.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.53,0:44:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAll we know is that if you calibrate Christianity in the first century, it calibrates at 950.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.04,0:44:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you calibrate it after the Council of Nicaea, it calibrates like, I don't know, 500 or something like that.\NSome huge loss of spiritual truth occurred at the Council of Nicaea.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.64,0:45:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the dark forces on the planet saw Christianity as a grave threat and somehow infiltrated into the Council of Nicaea and got some kind of a gain, some kind of a power, and decreased the...\Nthe... the...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.64,0:45:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of truth of the teaching.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.08,0:45:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't happen to... Buddhism still calibrates at a very high level, still calibrates almost at that source.\NSo other religions did not take such a huge hit. Somehow Christianity must have been a very grave threat. So it took a very heavy hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.43,0:45:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd... All right, so out of religiosity then, people that are more advanced begin to leave the negativity inherent in Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.56,0:45:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThe negativity inherent in that religion and adhere only to the universally true spiritual principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.75,0:45:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual principles of all religions are exactly the same.\NThe basic spiritual principles of all religions are exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.99,0:46:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens is the more advanced seeker leaves religion and... and becomes involved in spirituality.\NIt's like spirituality is the foundation of truth out of which all religions are built.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.50,0:46:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThe religion itself becomes taken over by the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.56,0:46:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ambitions for worldly power, worldly gain, to establish theocracies where they can rule the country, influence in owning endless property, political power.\NSo what happens is then the spiritual truths become corrupted by their practitioners, who then in the name of the spiritual truth, you know, violate... violate the... the spirit of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.74,0:46:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you see the letter of the law violating the spirit of the law.\NYou see, you know, Christian judgmentalism in its fundamentalist sects, you know, violating.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.76,0:47:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ said that the basic law is one of forgiveness, to love your neighbor.\NWell, if that's the basic law of Christianity, then how can you justify condemning your neighbor, stoning your neighbor, putting him to death, executing him, hanging him, putting him in an electric chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.46,0:47:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's wrong.\NHe's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.46,0:47:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Society needs to protect himself from that person.\NBut who gave anyone divine authority to execute another human being?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.46,0:47:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever gave it to any human being.\NOkay, David, let's go back to the reincarnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.72,0:47:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo you as a person believes it about many lifetimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.72,0:47:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can discover this for themselves.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.72,0:47:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you...\NYou could use kinesiology and ask, have I had previous lifetimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.72,0:47:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo you can begin to track them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.72,0:47:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you could see, hmm, can I remember anything about that?\NAnd there are many teachers that teach self-hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.84,0:48:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can go and out-of-body techniques, out-of-body astral projection techniques.\NThere's all kinds of teachers that will teach you astral projection techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.91,0:48:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can go into various lifetimes and re-experience yourself as various things, you know, at various times.\NAnd then you can puzzle over whether that literally happened or whether that only happened in one's unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.16,0:48:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.39,0:48:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore it's a puzzle for everyone.\NActually, it's not of any importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.39,0:48:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NReincarnation is of no importance whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.39,0:48:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the way to God is in this absolute moment.\NIn the absolute reality of this split second of now is the open, is the gateway.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.74,0:48:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThrough this moment now, you split the universe asunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.00,0:48:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I split the universe asunder right in this instant.\NAll time stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.89,0:48:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All form stops.\NI'm beyond the world and all of its doings in this very instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.89,0:49:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too interesting what went on in previous lifetimes.\NWell, but I see one maybe benefit to accepting those notions because in a way,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.37,0:49:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if, imagine,\Nthis is not the only human life I can have, then you can, it's just my interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.40,0:49:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but I feel people can more easily detaching themselves from all these, you know, cravings or desires for life.\NYou see, without some idea about previous lifetimes, a thoughtful person would eventually become an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.97,0:49:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NI'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.97,0:49:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you explain the newborn infant who was crushed under a cement truck?\NHow do you describe that the next one is born crippled?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.97,0:49:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you explain the next one is born gifted and a genius?\NHow would all these things be explained?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.64,0:50:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.25,0:50:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very easy if something painful happens in your life, you just say,\Nwell, it must be payback for something, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.41,0:50:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a horrible marriage, your wife treats you terribly, she cheats on you and beats you up\Nand lies about you and she's paranoid and delusional.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.41,0:50:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can say to yourself, well, I must have been a son of a gun in some lifetime.\NOtherwise, I would want to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.41,0:50:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NBecause in this lifetime, you've done nothing to justify this kind of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.70,0:50:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there's previous lifetimes, you could say, well, I must have created some kind of karma for myself\Nand I will do the best I can to live it through without complaining, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.92,0:50:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept it and do the best I can.\NAnd another teaching from the Buddha or the karma or the reincarnation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.15,0:51:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they're emphasized if in your own life paths anybody encountering you,\Nthen you'd better do your best no matter what these people do for you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.63,0:51:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because then it's the way you can cleaning your past karma between the two.\NI think that's kind of good.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.63,0:51:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And a wise way to keeping the relationship, handle the relationship.\NI think, you know, it's like you're given a chance to choose again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.88,0:51:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So somebody does evil towards you, now you've got your choice.\NYou can seek revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.88,0:51:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can come from the spleen.\NYou can choose hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.88,0:51:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose killing them.\NYou can choose condemning them morally even though you don't do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.33,0:51:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can choose forgiving them.\NAnd out of compassion for the weaknesses of human nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.33,0:51:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say, look, it's only human.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.33,0:52:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Also in relation to moving up toward the spiritual evolution,\Nyou know, many people say it is not safe to do that journey all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.33,0:52:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NSo then the question is what is the role of the teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.33,0:52:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual guru or the spiritual teacher?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.33,0:52:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As a student, as, you know, whatever, whoever you are,\Nyou want to do this kind of evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.33,0:52:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,can you tell me about the sort of image of proper true teacher?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.40,0:52:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's very important.\NIt's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.78,0:52:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Western world is rife with false teachers,\Nrife with teachers who are in error,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.61,0:52:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,rife with teachers who are wrongly motivated,\Nseeking worldly power and gain, notoriety.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.44,0:52:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Teachers get on television and become televangelists.\NSend me your money, send me your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.44,0:53:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is a true teacher then?\NA true teacher is not interested in any gain whatsoever,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.14,0:53:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't charge any money.\NThere's no money to charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.43,0:53:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth is a gift from God,\Nso how could you charge for that which was a gift to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.78,0:53:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the best thing the teacher can be is to be what he is to the student,\Nto be to the student,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.81,0:53:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to radiate out that energy of benevolence and love\Nthat supports the student through the difficulties that you know are ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.16,0:53:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt takes a very intense dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.16,0:53:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A very intense surrender.\NA true teacher knows it has nothing at all to do with his personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.16,0:54:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with this person as an individual.\NWhat has been revealed to you, you then transmit to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.15,0:54:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you only teach a teaching and explain to others how this comes about\Nand encourage them and enthuse them and support them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.47,0:54:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't lie to them.\NTell them it's going to be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.95,0:54:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,However, however, there is within oneself a drive\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.59,0:54:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to know God that is so powerful that once it is unleashed,\Nnothing will stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.59,0:54:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You will give away everything in the world.\NWhen I went through that phase, I gave away everything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.39,0:54:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the biggest psychiatric practice in the United States.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.39,0:54:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a huge estate which I myself designed and built on 35 acres in the Gold Coast.\NI had a Fifth Avenue apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.55,0:54:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had every kind of...\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.55,0:54:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the director of this and the board of that.\NIt all went out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.09,0:54:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaningless.\NAbsolutely meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.09,0:55:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in personal gain\Nbecause once you see that you're the source of all things,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.67,0:55:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like you have the formula for gold.\NThere's no point to pile up gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.67,0:55:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to have 50 Mercedes Benz cars.\NThere's no point to have 50...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.67,0:55:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that one guru we had in Washington there?\NHe had a Rajneesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.63,0:55:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\N75 very expensive cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.14,0:55:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.14,0:55:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.78,0:55:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the point of that?\NThe point is to be what you are to the student
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.45,0:55:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because what you are powerfully energizes the student,\Nwhat you are to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.05,0:55:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you hold in mind that enlightenment is a certainty for this person.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.28,0:55:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolute certainty.\NBecause once the desire to know God takes you over,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.76,0:56:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the end is certain.\NOnce you desire enlightenment, the Buddha said that too,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.01,0:56:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is true.\NWhy is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.04,0:56:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll tell you why it's so.\NThe average person who lives in time and space thinks that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.72,0:56:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what they are now is the creation of their past.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.72,0:56:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, I am what I am because my past made me that.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.54,0:56:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's being victim of one's past.\NNo such thing is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.54,0:56:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You can turn it around and say, oh, no,\Nit's what you are destined to become in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.99,0:56:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that is pulling you into what you are doing now.\NIt's because you're destined to become enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.05,0:56:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why you're interested in spiritual techniques and principles.\NIf you weren't destined to be enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.24,0:56:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you be doing on a spiritual pathway?\NIt would be of no interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.24,0:56:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The future is pulling you with absolute certainty.\NSo the person who is interested in enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.01,0:57:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say, well,\Nyou can say I guarantee you'll reach enlightenment all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.27,0:57:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise you wouldn't be searching for it, you know.\NThe future is already seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.36,0:57:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore all you do is try to make the path easier.\NThere are many different pathways, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.06,0:57:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think the other thing is not to make any other pathway wrong.\NIt's not that the pathway is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.35,0:57:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Right and wrong is meaningless.\NIt's that certain pathways are going to be more,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.73,0:57:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,more effective than others.\NSo that getting caught up in esotericism,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.83,0:57:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,psychic phenomena, psychic readings,\Nplaying with crystals,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.12,0:57:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to influence entities on the other side,\Nit's not that it's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.36,0:57:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Tibetan Buddhism gets caught in that,\Ntrying to create and detract entities from the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.61,0:58:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and then learn how to control them and disappear them\Nand make them do your bidding and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.61,0:58:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a grave distraction, you see.\NAnd also you're playing with fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.69,0:58:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, David, would you rather say\Nyou have your own spiritual teacher on your path or?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.95,0:58:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual teacher is a whole subject, you know,\Nand we could talk for an hour about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.87,0:58:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the teacher is one who has experienced the truth\Nto a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.24,0:58:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's why I say always calibrate a teacher\Nbecause you know what level this teacher is talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.34,0:58:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,First thing you want to make sure is that the teacher\Ndoesn't make you go weak with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.34,0:58:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to pick out false teachers.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.77,0:58:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the function of the teacher?\NFirst of all, the teacher's love for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.32,0:59:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,if he's a true teacher,\Nis so intense that if he revealed it to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.67,0:59:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it would frighten you.\NSo one thing I had to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.05,0:59:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was how to\NI guess the word would be disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.62,0:59:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How to\Npart of being ordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.72,0:59:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is to keep things within\Nthe common experience of human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.75,0:59:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when the state first came on,\Nit would have a profound effect on people.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.74,0:59:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't control it.\NI loved them with such intensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.35,0:59:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They were so incredibly beautiful.\NTheir divinity shone forth
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.85,0:59:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was in love with divinity.\NAnd it would actually blow them away,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.94,0:59:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, frighten them.\NOr they would fall in love with you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.94,1:00:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and think it was personal love or something.\NSo the first thing the teacher does is inspire you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.22,1:00:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and represents what is possible.\NAnd where is the teacher?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.98,1:00:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher is within oneself.\NThat drive to know God
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.98,1:00:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the God within oneself.\NTo get in touch with God within oneself,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.98,1:00:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,God wanting to know its own self,\NGod wanting to know its own Godness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.13,1:00:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and its expression here\Nis the Guru.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.71,1:00:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Guru is the drive to know the truth,\Nto know reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.71,1:00:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to become one with all that is again.\NIt may seek an external,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.51,1:00:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it may take the form of an external representation.\NI think one is inspired from unseen realms
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.33,1:00:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with.\NI think that,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.91,1:01:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but within the physical domain,\Nthe teacher would take, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.07,1:01:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,one who appeals to you\Nand whose truth you've already experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.32,1:01:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitively, let's say,\Nbut it's not complete.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.42,1:01:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me, the teachers that were attractive\Nwere Ramana Maharshi,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.84,1:01:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nisargadatta Maharaj,\Nthe Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.00,1:01:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po,\NJesus Christ in his true representation.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.09,1:01:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, what is his true representation\Nas infinite, unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.32,1:01:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that that implies.\NAnd all the great spiritual teachers throughout time
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.31,1:01:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I identify with.\NIf I read Meister Eckhart,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.56,1:01:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that level of awareness.\NIf I read the struggle of any of the great saints in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.60,1:01:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So every great teacher that's ever lived,\Nif I become acquainted with their teaching,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.60,1:02:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand exactly what they're talking about.\NAnd if they talk about a certain point of evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.84,1:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in their own consciousness,\NI've been through that and I recognize the truth of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.84,1:02:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So one true teacher can recognize\Nthe truth of another teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.84,1:02:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain things that you experience\Nat certain states which no one knows about.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.84,1:02:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Only another teacher understands this.\NEven the physical body reacts differently, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.64,1:02:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, I noticed that the startle response,\Nonce you stop identifying with the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.64,1:02:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed that the startle response disappears.\NFor instance, I was reminded of that yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.05,1:02:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a fierce storm right over the house\Nand lightning was crashing all around.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.05,1:02:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And a loud peal of thunder\Nsounded like it hit the house almost.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.31,1:02:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cat, the cat jumped up like this\Nand I noticed that this physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.31,1:03:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't react at all.\NYou see, you don't identify with the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.31,1:03:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so it doesn't respond to shock anymore.\NI'd say that the teacher then has nothing to gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.97,1:03:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So beware any teacher who has anything to gain.\NYou see, you're complete and total within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.58,1:03:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need compliments from anybody.\NYou don't need believers.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.58,1:03:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's totally irrelevant whether anybody believes\None word of what you say. That's their problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.48,1:03:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no material gain to be gotten.\NYou're complete and total.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.70,1:03:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have no needs that anybody could fulfill.\NIf you asked me what I would like for Christmas,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.89,1:03:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell you because I would only think of something\Nthat would make you happy, that I, Intuit,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.89,1:03:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,might be happy for you to give me,\Nthat would make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.89,1:03:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need anything at all.\NSo the teacher who looks for recognition or gain
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.47,1:03:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or to make his name famous,\Nthe book Power vs. Force,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.53,1:04:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I regretfully had to put a name on it.\NIt was really written by anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.53,1:04:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The awarenesses that came to me were a gift from God.\NIt came through this physicality,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.88,1:04:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so you would have to give it a label.\NYou would have to put a name on it and some degrees on it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.88,1:04:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the credibility problem in the human society.\NSo one reason I went to get a PhD
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.27,1:04:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was to give greater firepower to the truth of what I was saying.\NThey figured, well, an MD says this,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.27,1:04:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but an MD PhD, maybe it's even truer.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.27,1:04:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figure I'm a doctor doctor that way.\NThere must be some truth in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.27,1:04:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not only a doctor, he's a doctor doctor.\NDouble credit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.27,1:04:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that do anything for me?\NNothing at all, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.27,1:04:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so every instant is complete and total and perfect.\NEvery instant is already complete and total and perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.54,1:05:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So a true teacher would have no need for anything.\NYou don't have a need for followers.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.02,1:05:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have a need for titles.\NYou don't have a need for fancy anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.02,1:05:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason to have a bigger house\Nis if you have more guests
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.76,1:05:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then you need a bigger space to entertain.\NI used to have a great big house.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.76,1:05:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual groups used to meet there almost every weekend.\NSo we would have 50 people stay overnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.82,1:05:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,15 people stay overnight.\NI'll have breakfast in bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.82,1:05:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So I needed servants and I needed three gatehouses\Nand a huge house.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.82,1:05:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in those days, that's what I did.\NWe would have visiting speakers speak
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.43,1:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and teach about various things,\Nlike rebirthing or the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.88,1:05:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a member of the Zen...\NMeditation?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.91,1:05:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the First Zen Institute in America.\NI was a consultant to the Zen Institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.20,1:05:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a consultant to the Zen Monastery.\NI was a consultant also to the Episcopal Diocese.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.20,1:06:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the Episcopal Diocese and the Catholic Diocese.\NSo I used to see Episcopal priests and nuns
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.20,1:06:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and Catholic priests and nuns\Nand monks.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.61,1:06:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I came from the Zen Monastery.\NAnd my purpose then was to differentiate
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.70,1:06:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the aberrations that can arise\Nthrough intensive spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.30,1:06:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to recontextualize that back to the person.\NSo you can still find God even if you are psychotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.56,1:06:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the general understanding would be\Nif meditation is making you psychotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.13,1:06:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but I would say you can use the psychosis\Nto find God the same as any other material,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.13,1:06:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,any other conscious material.\NIf your problem is hallucinations and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.13,1:06:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a problem to the world,\Nbut it's not really a way of interfering,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.13,1:06:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of your getting to God,\Nbecause it's another vanity you're going to have to let go of.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.13,1:06:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're seeking non-duality,\Nthen all form is duality,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.13,1:07:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,including hallucinations, you see.\NSo you can use whatever material
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.13,1:07:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and it still serves the purpose of reaching\Nthe awareness of the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.13,1:07:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does a true teacher do?\NHe helps you along the pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.13,1:07:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience the presence of God\Nand the truth of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.13,1:07:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and reinforces that commitment and drive.\NTo reach the state of enlightenment itself
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.13,1:07:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,can make great demands.\NIt can ask you to sacrifice everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.38,1:07:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You accomplish everything in the world\Nand it says, now give it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.38,1:07:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to give it up.\NYou just, oh, God wants it, take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.48,1:07:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the willingness to surrender everything to God.\NBut then, you know, you were talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.05,1:07:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,certain spiritual techniques, yes,\Nthey require a drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.05,1:07:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You were saying that not everyone\Nhas the capacity to do that. That's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.88,1:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So maybe in some lifetimes\Na person develops this one-pointedness of mind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.88,1:08:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and this spiritual commitment,\Nthis drive to go through everything and anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.88,1:08:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See, 10,000 fall to the left of you\Nand 10,000 fall to the right, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.88,1:08:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is, you're walking a razor's edge.\NIt's a razor's edge, it is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.43,1:08:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And temptations arise because as you advance,\Nwhat you do is you summon forth its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.43,1:08:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're always confronted\Nwith what barrier you're up against.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.43,1:08:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the drive to walk through every single fear,\Nyou know yourself from meditative practice,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.36,1:08:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all the endless fears that arise,\Nthe fears that you're going crazy,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.36,1:08:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the fears of psychosis, the fears...\NEach fear has to be walked into,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.34,1:08:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I found that one teaching from Zen\Nwas extremely valuable,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.34,1:09:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is to always walk straight forward,\Nright through anything and everything that arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.08,1:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were moments of hesitation\Nwhen that teaching was of great value.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.46,1:09:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what the teacher himself\Nhas been doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.84,1:09:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what he's been through and shares with you,\Ncan be critical at a given moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.08,1:09:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's times when you reach a mental and psychic exhaustion,\Nand at that point you cannot stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.08,1:09:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At the point that you cannot go one iota further,\Nyou must go through that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.24,1:09:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, what happens is you break barriers.\NSo in meditative practice, you enter a new domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.24,1:09:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,filled with ecstasy.\NThere's always ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.62,1:09:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When you break through a new paradigm,\Nthere's always ecstasy, ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.62,1:10:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that you have conquered that domain,\Nand you've now emerged into a new and higher plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.88,1:10:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always that ecstasy,\Nand then, you know, the desire to share that ecstasy and joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.39,1:10:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you find that there's heavens beyond that heaven,\Nand then there's heavens beyond that heaven,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.03,1:10:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's heavens beyond that heaven.\NAnd so 850 then represents to me, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.73,1:10:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's the level of this consciousness now, a barrier.\NWhat is the barrier at 850?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.85,1:10:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?\NSo the teacher doesn't say to himself,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.72,1:10:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,hey, look how wonderful I am that I've traveled this far on the road,\Nbecause he knows it's only a road.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.32,1:10:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He says to himself, how come I'm only at 850?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.32,1:10:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the problem here?\NAll right, so you can stop for a moment with your spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.36,1:10:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and just be what you are to the world\Nand fulfill whatever the obligation is there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.74,1:11:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the teacher sees himself as obligated, in quotes, to others.\NHe sees no obligation of others to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.48,1:11:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So a teacher will give you everything he's got\Nand expects nothing to be repaid.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.92,1:11:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't owe me anything.\NI'll spend the next 10 years talking to you around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.52,1:11:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of that time, you owe me nothing.\NOkay, then, David, would you say you have some teachers
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.37,1:11:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or you've gone through all these paths by yourself?\NPrimarily, I was by myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.46,1:11:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three or four, that was by myself.\NGod has been my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.45,1:11:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My teacher is the Lord God himself.\NAnd in prayer throughout my lifetime, it's been to the Lord God himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.00,1:12:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how about would you then call yourself\Na spiritual teacher for people?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.12,1:12:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I call myself that.\NWhat I am is a sharer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.60,1:12:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I share with the world what I've learned, see,\Nfor whatever value it may be to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.80,1:12:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To some degree, statistically, what I've experienced is rare.\NTherefore, I say to share it with the world is valuable
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.32,1:12:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because it rarely happens.\NAnd then it rarely happens in a person with a scientific training
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.32,1:12:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,who can then come back into the world,\Nand then visualize it in such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.32,1:12:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can be comprehended through the intellect.\NUsually, a teacher says to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.37,1:12:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,drop everything, follow me, sit down, meditate,\Nlet the mind go, and call me in ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.76,1:13:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NOr the spiritual seeker reaches a state of exquisite bliss
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.08,1:13:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and stays there.\NSo there has to be a willingness to sacrifice even bliss itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.15,1:13:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the bliss state,\Nyou cannot really say anything to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.16,1:13:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the bliss state, you are that to the world.\NLet's say if you reach a state that calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.93,1:13:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A person at 600 probably counterbalances\N10 million people's negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.38,1:13:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if the monk who reaches 600\Ndoes nothing but sit in a state of bliss in a cave,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.38,1:13:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,he is already serving the world.\NBy his own existence, he radiates out that energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.41,1:13:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I was going down I-17,\Nand I felt this kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.70,1:13:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up the back and going through\Nand then out through the heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.50,1:14:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, that energy was accomplishing\Ncertain things within the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.92,1:14:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\NSo even if I just sat in my car and did nothing,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.92,1:14:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so you were like a broadcast station.\NSo somebody, some people out there are praying,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.92,1:14:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the nearest broadcast station radiates out this energy,\Ndivine love through, you know, serves
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.33,1:14:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's willing to be a channel of God's will.\NSo I think one of the most powerful prayers, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.65,1:14:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is to repeat that one is a servant of God.\NYou say, I am the servant of the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.65,1:14:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore my will, my thoughts and all that are of no use.\NTo be a servant of the Lord and then to ask God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.35,1:14:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to express His will for you, in what way\Ncan I be your servant of the Lord, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.35,1:14:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So then God perfects you\Nbecause you have now become His problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.31,1:15:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,His instrument, why don't we say that?\NHis problem, I say His problem, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.31,1:15:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because now His problem is how to make a better instrument out of you.\NSo when you say, you know, it's like a cat that declares
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.50,1:15:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that your home is His home now,\Nnow you've got to feed Him, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.50,1:15:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I call that rattling the gates of heaven.\NThe way you rattle the gates of heaven
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.50,1:15:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is you tell God you're His servant\Nand He'd better do something about it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.50,1:15:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you pester Him with prayers and supplications\Nand finally, you know, Ramana Maharshi says,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.50,1:15:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, finally God feels sorry for you\Nand gives you what you pray for.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.50,1:15:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you know, He's joking on one level.\NOn another level, He's very serious
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.50,1:15:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because, you know, you start rattling the gates of heaven\Nand you might say God now has to pay attention to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.79,1:15:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's this idiot out there claiming He's your servant\Nand you have to do something about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.27,1:16:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. See, at almost the end of your story,\Nyou said you had a very exquisite, another awakening.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.27,1:16:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You said, suddenly, without warning, a shift in awareness occurred.\NThe Presence was there unmistakably, all-encompassing.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.27,1:16:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There were few moments of apprehension\Nas the self died.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.27,1:16:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NSo I guess maybe this is the most dramatic experience you had.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.43,1:16:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So my curiosity is, can we calibrate which level it is?\NThat level there, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.64,1:16:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBecause it is...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.00,1:16:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in other words, you can move from the first great shock.\NWell, it takes quite a while to get used to the high 500s
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.44,1:16:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're surrounded now by perfection and beauty and synchronicity.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.44,1:16:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that life has really changed.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.44,1:16:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And people seek you out and they seek to be in your company.\NAnd the miraculous begins to occur, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.73,1:17:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's that paradigm shock to go through.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.73,1:17:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if you get into a spiritual practice\Nthat takes you out of duality into non-duality,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.80,1:17:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you're confronted with a whole other paradigm of reality\Nthat you have to get used to and you have to learn how to function
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.80,1:17:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and your problems with pronouns.\NYou know, who is the I?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.80,1:17:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no I.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.80,1:17:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But the I that you're experiencing is more profoundly I\Nthan the I which is capitalized.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.80,1:17:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which denotes the ego is supplanted.\NSee, what people fear is they're going to lose that I.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.80,1:17:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It disappears.\NBut an I that is more profoundly myself takes its place and continues on.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.81,1:17:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were asking me what?\NWell, in the almost close to the end, you were mentioning about...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.81,1:17:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, that question.\NOh, yes, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.81,1:17:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it sounds like a total seize of your ego.\NYes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.88,1:17:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask what that is.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.71,1:18:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment of the great unfolding,\Nthe energy which unfolded before me,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.76,1:18:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, it's self-revealing.\NThat which was self-revealing calibrates over 800 resist,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.89,1:18:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,850 resist, 860 resist, 900 resist, 800 resist,\N850 resist, 860 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.65,1:18:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,870 resist.\N880 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.65,1:18:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,890 resist.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.65,1:18:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somewhere in the high 800s.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.65,1:18:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NWe would have to take time out and really calibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.65,1:18:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, and then you mentioned your big spiritual task in this lifetime\Nis to see whether God is the nothingness, the void, or the allness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.96,1:18:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It turned out to be that that was the question.\NTo be honest, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.96,1:18:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NThat was the question to be answered.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.96,1:19:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt was interesting because somebody who sat in one of my lectures suddenly recovered
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.31,1:19:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from the illness that he had, and it was quite a profound experience.\NIt just happened during the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.98,1:19:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Six weeks later, a truck backed up, and this table which sits here, which weighs several\Nhundred pounds, he delivered.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.43,1:19:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He made this table himself out of a slab from the top of the mountain.\NIt's solid juniper.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.43,1:19:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a magnificent.\NHe made it as a bench.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.49,1:19:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's far too good as a bench.\NI said, oh, I need a table for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.56,1:19:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used it as a table.\NBut in the top, curiously, is Sanskrit, the symbols for allness and nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.56,1:19:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that was interesting how it suddenly appeared.\NSo I'm like confronted with, you know, the ancient problem of Hinayana versus Mahayana.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.56,1:19:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.72,1:19:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm like, well, I'm going to do it.\NI'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.72,1:19:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do it.\NI'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.72,1:19:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do it.\NI'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.72,1:19:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do it.\NI'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.72,1:19:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do it.\NI'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.72,1:19:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm like confronted with, you know, the ancient problem of Hinayana versus Mahayana.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.42,1:20:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, God as void.\NNow, the difficulty with a lot of spiritual work is that it's mistranslated from the Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.50,1:20:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo the ideal is not detachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.50,1:20:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an error.\NDetachment will take you to the void.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.50,1:20:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThe correct technique is nonattachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.53,1:20:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.53,1:20:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonattachment allows me to participate in life and be totally at one with it.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.53,1:20:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have nothing to gain from it and nothing to lose from it.\NConsequently, I can 100% participate without getting caught by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.53,1:20:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDetachment means I'm afraid of the world that if I get involved, I'll get caught by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.60,1:20:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.60,1:20:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Detachment is like the old story.\NPlease do not give me a cat because if you give me a cat, the cat will have to have milk.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.72,1:20:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIf the cat has to have milk, then I have to have a cow.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.72,1:20:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIf I have to have a cow, I have to milk the cow.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.72,1:20:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I have to have a fence to keep the cow in.\NThen I have to have food to feed the cow.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.72,1:20:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThen I have to get a job to get the money to buy the food to feed the cow.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.72,1:20:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do not give me a cat.\NThere's some sense of fear, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.72,1:21:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fear of being caught in the world.\NSo there's the phobia about relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.72,1:21:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd the monk has become celibate and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.72,1:21:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause he's going to get caught by sex.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.72,1:21:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NHe's going to get caught.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.72,1:21:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to get trapped by his ...\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.72,1:21:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,... by maleness, femaleness.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.72,1:21:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the monk is going to become celibate and all.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.72,1:21:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's going to get caught by sex.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.72,1:21:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to get caught.\NHe's going to get trapped by his ...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.72,1:21:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\N... by maleness, femaleness, and the attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.76,1:21:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWell, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.76,1:21:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay for the monk for a period of time.\NBut the sage, the sage who has reached a high state and now comes back in the world, has
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.76,1:21:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to participate again in life.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.79,1:21:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be able to handle money without getting caught by greed.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.01,1:21:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NRamakrishna, you know, Ramakrishna.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.01,1:21:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.01,1:21:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.01,1:21:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.01,1:21:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.01,1:21:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.01,1:21:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.20,1:21:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.20,1:21:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramakrishna.\NI experienced a lot of what Ramakrishna, you know, he went into the ecstasy and the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.14,1:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God.\NI went to that same ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.14,1:21:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood Ramakrishna very well.\NBut he would only take young men as students.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.00,1:22:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing I never agreed with him is he would always say the root of all problems\Nis money and women, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.68,1:22:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Money and sex.\NMoney and sex.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.82,1:22:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So he forbid either one.\NYou weren't even allowed to touch money, much less think about sex or look at the opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.74,1:22:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,sex.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.18,1:22:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nenlightened means that one has lost all fear of you must be able to walk through life participating
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.26,1:22:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,fully you must be able to eat meat without thinking that your soul is going to go to hell\Nthat you have just killed an animal see because you've brought the animal life the cow the cattle
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.83,1:22:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,would not even exist except for the fact that you eat them if you stop everybody stops eating cattle\Nno more cattle will be born because nobody will buy cattle nobody will raise cattle
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.93,1:22:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the cute little cows out there won't get to moo and eat grass you still have no reason to\Ncome into existence you understand so when you reach the full understanding of things
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.59,1:23:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no reason to avoid them okay all right so don't get caught by them\Nis different so detachment is different than non-attachment so even a small thing so you'll
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.25,1:23:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,see in buddha's literature there's a misunderstanding of the buddha's teaching about that let's let's\Ncheck out the truth of what we just said the correct spiritual teaching to reach um the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.22,1:23:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of the presence of god is detachment resist the correct spiritual technique is\Nnon-attachment resist all right so we have confirmation of what i just said yes it's by
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.13,1:23:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,being non-attached i can participate fully with you right if i'm detached i would be indifferent\Ni'd say she wants to write a book about it that's her problem and i wouldn't even give you an
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.85,1:23:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,appointment\Ni'm detached from you and what you're up to and i have no interest in anything outside of reaching
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.11,1:24:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,my own enlightenment so you see how detachment leads eventually to a spiritual egocentricity\Nand that's the downside of the hinayana pathway right that i'm only interested in my enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.95,1:24:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and your suffering is just an illusion see so did they not deny the reality of suffering to the\Nperson who suffers is a spiritual error see
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.31,1:24:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so the one difficulty with being in its 720 or something you say well all that is illusion out\Nthere that's just a projection and it has no reality so i don't have to get involved in helping
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.31,1:24:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,relieve human suffering because it has no reality human suffering is very real on its own level\Nand true its basis is illusion but that doesn't mean that it still doesn't fester and cause agony
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.48,1:24:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nhumankind to me is a spiritual error i'm very aware of this agony of humankind it's because
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.23,1:25:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the agony of humankind that i come back into the world and write a book and and appear with\Nyou today it's because of that agony out of compassion for that agony so to show people
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.19,1:25:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the way out of that agony you know is is mankind serving its own purpose\Nso it's the suffering of mankind that pulls this entity here back into the world and back
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.52,1:25:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,into practice and writing books and appearing to try to explain things just you know just a\Nsimple thing to see that the cause of anger is not about what people are but what they are not
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.30,1:25:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that itself can make such a change in your life just that little notion you understand that i'm\Nangry at the car not because it breaks down but because it it doesn't maintain itself you see
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.96,1:25:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so all\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.30,1:25:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Already that creates a shift in consciousness.\NIt's that shift in consciousness that I seek to support, you know, in mankind in general.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.46,1:26:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the consciousness of mankind crossed over to the 200 line, it critical massed.\NSo the explanation of it from a scientific viewpoint is really chaos theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.22,1:26:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So things stay the same.\NSo the consciousness of mankind throughout centuries stayed at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.60,1:26:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate, what was it in the year 1400, 1500, 1600, 1700, what was it in the\Nyear 1100, you'll come up, it was 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.00,1:26:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind stayed at 190, which is below the critical level.\NTherefore, the survival of mankind was not at all guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.46,1:26:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, your survival is not guaranteed because that's less than integrity.\NThat which supports life was not as strong as that which was destructive of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.32,1:26:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The incarnation of life.\NInquisition was certainly a very good example, the dark ages, you know, in which negativity
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.49,1:26:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,prevailed.\NIt was the lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.49,1:27:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody lived past the age of 40.\NEverybody died of smallpox, syphilis, and destruction was rampant.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.99,1:27:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so chaos theory tells you that through iteration, the process of iteration, it is\Nthrough the process of sameness that difference suddenly arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.75,1:27:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So a difference of one digit in the 20 line.\NThe 26 decimal point will not make any difference tens of millions of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.36,1:27:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you repeat it tens of millions of times, all of a sudden, the fact that the 26 digit\Nis up or down one will suddenly throw a number that cannot even be predicted.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.02,1:27:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of millions and millions of lifetimes of black raccoons, all of a sudden, you'll\Nget a white one.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.02,1:28:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so out of the sameness of that 190, conventional thinkingness of the 20 line,\Nthe ego which prevailed, suddenly it's almost like it gets dissatisfied with itself and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.15,1:28:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it jumps itself.\NSo you know, just we could say mathematically speaking, from the viewpoint of chaos theory,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.32,1:28:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you could predict that if the consciousness of mankind stays at 190 century after century,\Nif you project far enough ahead in time, suddenly it will jump beyond 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.68,1:28:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is, if the human conscience is raising up 204.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.38,1:28:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be quite courageous in a way, because in a common sense, the pessimistic\Nview seems to be getting more stronger somehow.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.54,1:28:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, the pessimistic view is not really stronger.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.32,1:28:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always been there.\NAnd there's always the naysayers.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.19,1:28:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always the people that predict there's going to be more people on the planet than\Nthe planet can supply food, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.76,1:29:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it extrapolates into the future.\NThat which is in the present, which is an error.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.26,1:29:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a scientific error.\NIt's a mathematical error.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.66,1:29:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the future recreates itself.\NThe future constantly recreates itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.92,1:29:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And it finds solutions for itself.\NIt doesn't have to find a solution to the year 2020 now, it doesn't have to yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.26,1:29:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 2020, it'll come up with a bright solution to the problems of 2020.\NSo, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.64,1:29:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Malthus's prediction that the world could only hold so many million people and then\Nthey would begin to starve to death never came true.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.03,1:29:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is productivity per acre has quadrupled, in fact, I think it's gone up like tenfold.\NSo although the population may double, our agricultural productivity has gone up to such
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.51,1:29:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,an extent that the government pays us to not till millions of acres.\NThe way to get rich is to own millions of acres and do nothing with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.57,1:30:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the government will hand you all kinds of money, because there's too much food.\NSo our problem is we have too much food.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.76,1:30:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So Malthus was totally wrong.\NAnd so the thinkingness of Malthus-type people, you know, reemerges constantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.38,1:30:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees, you know, the negative potentiality of everything and then projects that and recreates.\NAnd creates negativity for us to live with.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.28,1:30:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the thought that nothing is possible.\NNothing is impossible, which was expressed by Christopher Reeves as a very correct thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.76,1:30:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of his politics.\NNothing is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.74,1:30:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So what seems impossible is an artifact of positionality.\NAnd when one transcends that, the answer is standing there clearly and obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.82,1:31:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no problem that mankind has that the answer doesn't already exist.\NAnd what would you reiterate?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.96,1:31:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NWhat would you anticipate the collective level of human consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.60,1:31:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be coming up?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.10,1:31:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It could stay.\NWhat did I say it was?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.10,1:31:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,204, 207?\NI forget the last time I calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.66,1:31:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that it'll probably stabilize there for a number of centuries.\NAnd then it will, like a lion getting ready for a leap, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.29,1:31:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The lion looks like he's not moving, see?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.67,1:31:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He crouches.\NIt looks like he's not moving, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.67,1:31:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, then when the lion leaps, now he's moving.\NOh, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.67,1:31:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He was moving already because he has to gather himself up.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.67,1:31:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the leap is only the end result of what's happened already.\NSo the great lion of society will again go into a crouch and begin to build up its power
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.33,1:31:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and strength, and it'll leap again.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.67,1:32:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll continue to leap.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.76,1:32:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the evolution of mankind will continue to leap.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.49,1:32:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once you're over 200, you're into the level of courage and integrity.\NWell, once you're into courage and integrity, the answers to everything from that point
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.23,1:32:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are discoverable.\NWhen you're below 200, you can't find the answer to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.47,1:32:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're over 200, it's only a matter of time before you find the answer to everything,\Nyou see.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.56,1:32:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhen your goal is only over 200, you have courage and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.72,1:32:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage and integrity will lead you to the fact that love solves about 99% of human problems.\NSo even if you're not at love yet, you discover that love has the power to heal.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.25,1:32:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.92,1:32:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.92,1:32:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.92,1:32:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.92,1:32:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.92,1:33:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.92,1:33:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
